tors are treated with some detail in Chapter 2. Prerequisites for a satisfactory reading of the present Notes are not only a course of Calculus for functions of one or several variables, but also a course in Mathematical Analysis where - among others - some basic knowledge of the topology of normed spaces is supposed to be included. For the reader's convenience some notions in this context are explicitly recalled here and there, and in particular as an Appendix in Section 1.4. An excellent reference for this general background material is W. Rudin's classic Principles of Mathematical Analysis. On the other hand, a complete discussion of the results on ODE and PDE that are here just sketched are to be found in other books, specifically and more deeply devoted to these subjects, some of which are listed in the Bibliography. In conclusion and in brief, my hope is that the present Notes can serve as a second quick reading on the theme of ODE, and as a first introductory reading on Fourier series, Hilbert spaces, and PDE  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aFolgen und Reihen von Funktionen. 4aLineare Systeme. 4aSkalarprodukt und Orthonormalsysteme. 4aTrigonometrische Reihe. 7aMATHEMATICS / Differential Equations / General.2bisacsh  aEquations of Mathematical Physics.  aLinear systems.  aOrthonormal systems.  aSequences and series of functions.  aTrigonometric series.0 cEPUBz97831113028670 cprintz978311129485840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311130252240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783111302522423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783111302522/original  aEBA_CL_CHCOMSGSEN  aEBA_CL_MTPY  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CHCOMSGSEN  aEBA_ECL_MTPY  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles